block lcontent
  h1 Qualifications
  p Interpreters listed on this website are fully qualified BSL/English Interpreters. RSLI after their name refers to a member of the Register of Sign Language Interpreters, held by the NRCPD (National Register of Communication Professionals working with Deaf and Deafblind People).
  p These interpreters have agreed to abide by a code of conduct and complaints procedure. They will have professional indemnity insurance and identification cards. RSLIâ€™s will also have a current enhanced DBS certificate available for you to check. 
    a(href="http://www.nrcpd.org.uk/") RSLI 
  p MVLP refers to a member of Visual Language Professionals. Members carry an ID card which clearly states that they are qualified. 
    a(href="https://www.vlp.org.uk/") VLP 
  p MASLI refers to a Full Member of the Association of Sign Language Interpreters
    a(href="https://www.asli.org.uk/")  ASLI 
  p *Qualifications are:
  ul
    li Postgraduate qualification in BSL/English interpreting (PGDIP or MA)
    li Signature Level 6 NVQ in Interpreting BSL/English (including Signature Level 4 NVQ BSL/English interpreting)
    li CACDP RQI exam (pre NVQ)

block rcontent
